ÕTHE LANTERN SEAT
THE 1818 BACK PANEL IN THIS SEAT WAS RESCUED BY
DONALD BAKER OF MEAD MILL ROMSEY DURING THE
DEMOLITION OF THE SOUNDING ARCH AT EMBLEY PARK
- THE HOME OF FLORENCE NIGHTINGALE (THE LADY OF
THE LAMP)
DON COMMISSIONED LOCAL BLACKSMITH RICHARD BENT
OF BRAISHFIELD TO DESIGN AND MAKE THE SEAT IN
THE SPRING OF 2004"ů
